We are implementing PathPlanner for the first time this year, and are struggling to get it working correctly. Every time a PathPlanner library function is called, for example “AutoBuilder::followPath()”, the robot code crashes due to a “bad function call” error. Does anyone know why this might be happening?

Here is our code: GitHub - cyberblue234/2024CB234

P.S. changing to command based is a last resort for us

The definition of followPath is this:

static frc2::CommandPtr followPath(std::shared_ptr<PathPlannerPath> path);

This function builds a command for the command-based framework to follow a path. It appears you’re trying to call it as a periodic function, which isn’t going to work.

It appears pathplannerlib is really designed for integration with command-based robot programs, and you’d have to essentially re-implement its path following implementation to use it in a timed robot.
